docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Feb. 20 -- Uruguay on a smaller scale is having the same experience as its neighbor, Argentina, in trying to reconstruct a broken down economy. Although this is one of Latin America's outstanding democracies, a spendthrift Government voted out of office last year left a pile of debts; habits of consumption based on subsidized prices for beef, transportation, fuels and luxury imports; and labor unions accustomed to getting what they demanded.
